\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {15}{\ignorespaces For each value of $\rho $, the closed-form $\mathbb  {E}[R_{pt}]$ (blue line), active component (red dashed) and passive component (green dashed) from~\eqref  {eq:lo26} are plotted against the threshold $\zeta $. Markers superimpose the simulated counterparts; the vertical bars on $\mathbb  {E}[R_{pt}]$ are 95\% Monte-Carlo confidence intervals. The simulation sits on top of the theoretical curves at every grid point.}}{27}{figure.caption.61}\protected@file@percent }
