\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {16}{\ignorespaces An illustrative sample path of length $T=240$ at $\rho =0.25$, $\zeta =0.0\%$. Top: the AR(1) strategy return $R_t$ with the threshold $\zeta $ (red dashed) and risk-free rate $R_f$ (green dotted). Orange-shaded periods mark the dates when $\omega _t=0$ (the portfolio holds $R_f$). Bottom: the resulting stop-loss portfolio return $R_{pt}$, which sits at $R_f$ exactly during the shaded periods.}}{28}{figure.caption.62}\protected@file@percent }
